    "creation_date" : 1487845630,
    "answer_id" : 42413023,
    "question_id" : 6355498,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>It could be due to below reasons: -</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li><p>Either you dont have INTERNET permission in manifest file. If so then please use this statement <code>&lt;uses-permission android:name=\"android.permission.INTERNET\" /&gt;</code></p></li>\n<li><p>Or you are connected to a network but your internet connection is not working. Like you are connected to a Wi-Fi but it doesnt have internet connection or Mobile data on your phone is ON but you dont have data connectivity on your phone. </p></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>Point# 2 is interesting and its not assumption, I have tested the same at my end.</p>\n\n<p>Hope this will help you</p>\n\n<p>Summved </p>\n"
  }, {
